                        <!--  *************************************  <handDesc>  ********************************* -->

                        <handDesc hands="1">
                            <handNote ana="#inscribed"> Both lines generally have some uneven
                                spacing between letters, particularly before omicrons such as
                                between the omicron and the rho of Διôσκόροις, between the lambda
                                and omicron in Λούκιος, between the sigma in Λούκιος and the omicron
                                in Οὐήλιος, and between the iota and omicron in Οὐήλιος. Line 1:
                                Διôσκόροις: the full spelling of the name has been shortened,
                                possibly through a lunate sigma with a bar across the top half,
                                signifying ligature of the omicron and sigma. This was perhaps to
                                keep the top line more center, as the beginning and end of the line
                                is perfectly couched by the figures of the Dioskoroi themselves.
                                Line 2: Φρόντων: the omega and nu are in ligature, with the final
                                stroke of the omega forming the first stroke of the nu.</handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <!--  *************************************  <decoDesc>  *********************************     -->
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote>
                                <p>The relief depicts an eagle in the tympanum and the Dioskoroi
                                    dressed in cuirasses, each holding the manes of their horses
                                    while flanking a female figure standing in the center of the
                                    relief. The inscription is carved into the lintel below the
                                    eagle above the three figures with the statement of offering,
                                    and concludes below them with the name of the dedicator. </p>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
